The '''operation chart''' is a [[graphical]] and [[symbol]]ic representation of the [[manufacturing]] operations used to produce a product.<ref>Groover, M. P. (2007). ''Work Systems: The Methods, Measurement & Management of Work'', Prentice Hall, {{ISBN|978-0-13-140650-6}}</ref> The operation chart illustrates only the [[value-adding]] activities in the [[manufacturing process]]; therefore, [[material handling]] and [[Warehouse|storage]] are not illustrated in this chart. operation chart records the overall picture of process and sequencewise steps of operations.

== Operations and their symbols in the operation chart ==
The operations described in the operation chart are:
#Processing and assembly operations: [[Process (engineering)|Processing]] operation such as changing in shape and properties. On the other hand, joining two or more parts is an [[Manufacturing|assembly]] operation. Furthermore, these two operations are represented by this symbols, circle (○) and (O) letter.
#Inspection operations: [[Inspection]] operations are represented by square symbol (□) and (I) as letter. It's done by an inspector checks the material, work part and assembly for quality and quantity.

